---
---

<section class="py-20" style="background-color:#16213e;">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-3" style="color:#ffffff;">Built with privacy in mind</h2>
    <p class="text-center mb-12" style="color:#a0a0b0;">Your voice. Your data. Your machine.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <!-- Audio flow -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[#2a3a5c] p-6" style="background-color:#1f2b47;">
        <div class="mb-4 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background-color:#1a4d4d;">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="#06b6d4" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
              d="M19 11a7 7 0 01-7 7m0 0a7 7 0 01-7-7m7 7v4m0 0H8m4 0h4m-4-8a3 3 0 01-3-3V5a3 3 0 116 0v6a3 3 0 01-3 3z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2" style="color:#ffffff;">Audio stays local by default</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:#a0a0b0;">
          With <code class="font-mono text-xs px-1 rounded" style="background-color:#131c30;color:#8b5cf6;">stt_engine = "local"</code>, audio never leaves your machine.
          Cloud engines (Deepgram, Groq) send audio only for transcription — the transcript itself is never uploaded.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Keychain -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[#2a3a5c] p-6" style="background-color:#1f2b47;">
        <div class="mb-4 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background-color:#2d1b69;">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="#8b5cf6" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
              d="M15 7a2 2 0 012 2m4 0a6 6 0 01-7.743 5.743L11 17H9v2H7v2H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-2.586a1 1 0 01.293-.707l5.964-5.964A6 6 0 1121 9z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2" style="color:#ffffff;">API keys in macOS Keychain</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:#a0a0b0;">
          Keys are stored in the system Keychain via the <code class="font-mono text-xs px-1 rounded" style="background-color:#131c30;color:#8b5cf6;">keyring</code> crate — never in plaintext config files or environment variables. Run <code class="font-mono text-xs px-1 rounded" style="background-color:#131c30;color:#0d9488;">chamgei key list</code> to inspect them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- No telemetry -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[#2a3a5c] p-6" style="background-color:#1f2b47;">
        <div class="mb-4 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background-color:#1a4d2e;">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="#22c55e" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
              d="M18.364 18.364A9 9 0 005.636 5.636m12.728 12.728A9 9 0 015.636 5.636m12.728 12.728L5.636 5.636"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2" style="color:#ffffff;">Zero telemetry</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:#a0a0b0;">
          No analytics, no crash reports, no usage pings. The binary doesn't make any network requests you haven't explicitly configured. Config and history files are chmod 0600.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
